please come to a ticket window or seek an attendant for your safety.

18
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:11,560
Do you wish... to be eaten by me?

19
00:05:17,670 --> 00:05:20,040
The train is coming to Platform 1.

20
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:23,260
Please wait behind the white line.

21
00:05:59,140 --> 00:06:02,000
They are moving around quite visibly.

22
00:06:03,020 --> 00:06:04,260
Shall we go?

23
00:06:04,850 --> 00:06:06,220
Wait a minute.

24
00:06:06,790 --> 00:06:08,970
Gone? Escaped?

25
00:06:08,970 --> 00:06:09,860
What?

26
00:06:09,860 --> 00:06:12,620
They said it was recaptured by another unit.

27
00:06:12,620 --> 00:06:13,180
Where?

28
00:07:42,770 --> 00:07:46,770
Who... who are you?

29
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:30,940
Confirming the target is destroyed.

30
00:08:31,540 --> 00:08:32,990
There are two witnesses.

31
00:08:32,990 --> 00:08:34,580
Recovery unit, hurry.

32
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:44,270
A dead body, dead body.

33
00:08:52,030 --> 00:08:54,760
You, who are you?

34
00:08:57,120 --> 00:08:58,900
Fujimura-kun?

35
00:09:02,470 --> 00:09:03,520
Mana-chan?

36
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:05,960
What? Hiiragi.

37
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:06,970
You...!

38
00:09:11,380 --> 00:09:13,440
This is the Old Ones.

39
00:09:14,270 --> 00:09:15,530
The Old Ones.

40
00:09:15,530 --> 00:09:17,520
Why are you here?

41
00:09:17,520 --> 00:09:18,910
Matsuo-kun.

42
00:09:18,910 --> 00:09:20,280
Fuji, let's get out of here.

43
00:09:20,280 --> 00:09:21,790
Y-Yes.

44
00:09:22,150 --> 00:09:22,790
Hiiragi.

45
00:09:35,520 --> 00:09:37,050
Dammit. Hurry up!

46
00:09:52,040 --> 00:09:52,830
Drive.

47
00:09:53,660 --> 00:09:54,780
What do you want?!

48
00:09:54,780 --> 00:09:55,660
You are...

49
00:09:55,660 --> 00:09:56,710
We'll be caught..

50
00:09:58,620 --> 00:09:59,160
Dammit!

51
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:16,000
Witnesses are escaping by car.

52
00:10:16,650 --> 00:10:18,010
We are now in pursuit.

53
00:10:18,810 --> 00:10:20,340
Ground units, hurry to the scene.

54
00:10:27,570 --> 00:10:28,760
They're chasing us!

55
00:10:29,470 --> 00:10:31,360
Point the way!

56
00:10:36,550 --> 00:10:38,860
Come in, SIRRUT, this is Fujimura.

57
00:10:38,860 --> 00:10:41,240
We are being chased by a Tower helicopter!

58
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:43,080
H-Help!

59
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:44,330
Yanagi-san!

60
00:10:44,690 --> 00:10:46,960
Calm down, Fujmura-kun.

61
00:10:48,750 --> 00:10:49,700
Yes.

62
00:10:50,170 --> 00:10:52,710
We will send you the escape route within one minute.

63
00:10:53,550 --> 00:10:57,490
Meanwhile, send us the information you have acquired.

64
00:10:57,490 --> 00:10:59,390
U-Understood.

65
00:10:59,390 --> 00:11:03,770
Tsuki-chan, gain control of the traffic system immediately.

66
00:11:03,770 --> 00:11:04,910
Yes.

67
00:11:04,910 --> 00:11:07,640
Also, hack into the District of Land and Transportation Bureaus' computer system.

68
00:11:08,580 --> 00:11:09,860
Yes.

69
00:11:12,020 --> 00:11:14,190
Is it all right, Mogari-san?

70
00:11:18,420 --> 00:11:19,230
Yes.

71
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:47,060
There!  Right, right!

72
00:11:47,060 --> 00:11:48,980
Stupid! That's a one-way street!

73
00:11:49,640 --> 00:11:51,460
I... I'm sorry.

74
00:11:55,040 --> 00:11:56,570
I've got the escape route.

75
00:11:57,320 --> 00:12:02,060
Ah, ahead, right at the traffic signal.

76
00:12:12,680 --> 00:12:14,080
That’s the wrong way!

77
00:12:13,270 --> 00:12:14,460
Shut up!

78
00:12:21,340 --> 00:12:23,540
We went off the route...

79
00:12:24,040 --> 00:12:25,870
Fuck the route!

80
00:12:27,390 --> 00:12:28,430
I'll get us back on track.

81
00:12:28,430 --> 00:12:29,560
Fuji-kun!

82
00:12:32,050 --> 00:12:34,130
Behind us! They are coming!

83
00:12:35,760 --> 00:12:36,860
It's not over!

84
00:12:37,880 --> 00:12:39,440
Yanagi-saaan!

85
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:41,400
Go on.

86
00:12:42,610 --> 00:12:44,910
Speed it up, now!

87
00:12:45,550 --> 00:12:47,400
Screw it, I don't care anymore!

88
00:13:00,430 --> 00:13:01,300
Now.

89
00:13:01,300 --> 00:13:02,380
Yes.

90
00:13:19,110 --> 00:13:20,620
It's over.

91
00:13:28,760 --> 00:13:29,940
We've got to keep going.

92
00:13:47,560 --> 00:13:48,580
There's blood...

93
00:13:49,330 --> 00:13:50,340
Lay off.

94
00:13:55,120 --> 00:13:58,060
Is that guy dead?

95
00:14:02,540 --> 00:14:04,750
I feel relieved now.

96
00:14:05,100 --> 00:14:09,740
My poor car is covered with scratches...

97
00:14:09,740 --> 00:14:11,600
It's the ultimate sacrifice.

98
00:14:12,880 --> 00:14:17,150
My name is Hiiragi Mana.

99
00:14:17,150 --> 00:14:18,350
What's yours?

100
00:14:18,350 --> 00:14:19,080
Huh?

101
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:22,010
Don’t you guys know each other?

102
00:14:22,010 --> 00:14:23,180
No.

103
00:14:23,180 --> 00:14:28,800
She just rescued me... from that scary guy.

104
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:30,730
S-She did?

105
00:14:30,730 --> 00:14:33,390
From Tower's Old Ones?

106
00:14:35,210 --> 00:14:38,040
Why do you know about the Old Ones?

107
00:14:39,550 --> 00:14:41,850
What are you guys doing?

108
00:14:43,030 --> 00:14:44,970
What is Tower?

109
00:14:45,680 --> 00:14:47,070
Who are they?

110
00:14:47,460 --> 00:14:52,980
That's what we want to know...

111
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:05,180
We are trying to expose the identity of Tower.

112
00:15:05,180 --> 00:15:09,000
Do you have a grudge against them?

113
00:15:11,140 --> 00:15:12,990
What happened back there?

114
00:15:13,640 --> 00:15:18,000
Why was that monster... dead?

115
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:23,050
Because I killed it.

116
00:15:26,870 --> 00:15:29,910
Who are you?

117
00:15:37,020 --> 00:15:38,570
It's from headquarters?

118
00:15:38,570 --> 00:15:39,740
From Yanagi-san?

119
00:15:42,270 --> 00:15:48,000
Kisaragi Saya, don't you wish to shoot Nanahara Fumito?

120
00:15:49,060 --> 00:15:50,340
Fumito...

121
00:15:56,150 --> 00:15:57,560
I am inviting you back to headquarters.

122
00:15:58,490 --> 00:16:01,440
We'll talk... then.

123
00:16:13,300 --> 00:16:16,300
The winner receives a reward...

124
00:16:17,250 --> 00:16:20,730
The loser receives punishment...

125
00:16:36,030 --> 00:16:37,420
Fumito-sama.

126
00:16:38,830 --> 00:16:41,150
The governor of Tokyo is
requesting a lunch meeting

127
00:16:41,150 --> 00:16:44,670
regarding the punishment of all those who violated the Juvenile Protection Curfew Ordinance,

128
00:16:44,670 --> 00:16:47,540
which has been in effect since last month.

129
00:16:48,520 --> 00:16:50,900
If you become the governor of Tokyo soon,

130
00:16:50,900 --> 00:16:55,540
there won't be a need for such wasteful meetings, Yuka-kun.

131
00:16:56,380 --> 00:16:58,110
I agree with you.

132
00:16:59,910 --> 00:17:01,670
How old are you now?

133
00:17:02,360 --> 00:17:03,770
28 years old.

134
00:17:04,360 --> 00:17:07,830
You were only a high-school student six months ago.

135
00:17:08,660 --> 00:17:12,700
You want to forget your bad memories quickly, don't you?

136
00:17:14,120 --> 00:17:17,050
I appreciate that you know how I feel.

137
00:17:17,670 --> 00:17:20,080
Next is the meeting with the Ambassador of the United States.

138
00:17:20,080 --> 00:17:22,740
He wishes to move up the meeting date.

139
00:17:23,840 --> 00:17:28,250
Recent appointments and reports are all like that...

140
00:17:28,250 --> 00:17:31,690
Considering the financial strength and influence of our company, Seventh Heaven,

141
00:17:31,690 --> 00:17:36,740
and the secret you and your family have been protecting,

142
00:17:36,740 --> 00:17:39,850
even this is not enough.

143
00:17:40,700 --> 00:17:42,420
You are ambitious.

144
00:17:43,280 --> 00:17:44,560
Fumito-sama.

145
00:17:45,170 --> 00:17:47,170
What happened, Kuto?

146
00:17:48,350 --> 00:17:52,000
The one that escaped from the laboratory was destroyed.

147
00:17:53,560 --> 00:17:56,200
We have finished recovery from inside of the subway,

148
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:59,890
but there are two witnesses.

149
00:17:59,890 --> 00:18:02,270
We were outmaneuvered?

150
00:18:03,760 --> 00:18:06,350
I disposed of the ones that let them escape.

151
00:18:06,350 --> 00:18:09,400
Next time, I will handle it personally.

152
00:18:10,210 --> 00:18:13,160
I don't think you'll be able to get them.

153
00:18:24,010 --> 00:18:25,790
Saya's showed up.

154
00:19:20,760 --> 00:19:22,210
We should be going.

155
00:19:46,160 --> 00:19:47,360
What's wrong?

156
00:19:48,770 --> 00:19:50,090
Come here quickly.

157
00:19:58,380 --> 00:19:59,260
Come in.

158
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:07,770
Hiiragi, I understand the situation.

159
00:20:07,770 --> 00:20:08,720
Y-Yes.

160
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:13,190
Welcome, Kisaragi Saya. I am Mogari Kuroto.

161
00:20:13,620 --> 00:20:15,980
Why do you know me?

162
00:20:17,560 --> 00:20:18,860
Ukishima.

163
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:25,620
An experiment took place there that killed all the residents.

164
00:20:31,330 --> 00:20:38,010
Brutality is the only word sufficient to describe the manner in which they were killed.

165
00:20:49,370 --> 00:20:54,990
However, there was one survivor from that experiment.

166
00:20:59,290 --> 00:21:02,160
It was you. Kisaragi Saya.

167
00:21:06,440 --> 00:21:09,320
Why do you have these?

168
00:21:09,960 --> 00:21:11,870
Itsuki sent these to me.

169
00:21:13,710 --> 00:21:18,000
He called himself Tomofusa Itsuki when he was talking to you, didn't he?

170
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:22,030
He hacked the Tower's surveillance cameras and kept sending us data,

171
00:21:22,030 --> 00:21:24,580
even if it was only bits and pieces.

172
00:21:25,370 --> 00:21:26,660
Is that person...

173
00:21:27,300 --> 00:21:33,300
He did not work with us, but he was a member of SIRRUT.

174
00:21:34,330 --> 00:21:35,670
Is Itsuki...?

175
00:21:35,670 --> 00:21:36,780
Dead.

176
00:21:39,120 --> 00:21:45,180
Itsuki participated in the Ukishima experiment in order to expose everything about Tower.

177
00:21:45,180 --> 00:21:46,100
Tower?

178
00:21:47,190 --> 00:21:51,200
An organization that Nanahara Fumito is secretly controlling.

179
00:21:51,200 --> 00:21:56,970
Officially, Fumito is a chairman of Seventh Heaven — a giant conglomerate,

180
00:21:56,970 --> 00:22:02,170
not only in Japan, but also in the rest of the world.

181
00:22:02,840 --> 00:22:05,420
He has strong political connections,

182
00:22:05,420 --> 00:22:11,360
and is said to have had a part in the new Juvenile Protection Curfew Ordinance.

183
00:22:11,360 --> 00:22:18,530
But the only thing he's interested in is that other organization.

184
00:22:18,530 --> 00:22:21,060
That is Tower?

185
00:22:21,060 --> 00:22:28,530
Fumito is trying to accomplish something using the power of both Seventh Heaven and Tower.

186
00:22:28,530 --> 00:22:29,640
Something?

187
00:22:29,640 --> 00:22:34,290
Unfortunately, we do not know exactly what that “something” is.

188
00:22:34,650 --> 00:22:39,710
But we know that many people have been killed because of it.

189
00:22:39,710 --> 00:22:46,260
And that things called “Old Ones” are involved.

190
00:22:46,940 --> 00:22:49,620
How do you know all this?

191
00:22:49,620 --> 00:22:55,370
Because I researched, using all my time, money and power.

192
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:56,680
Why?

193
00:22:57,510 --> 00:23:02,690
Because Nanahara Fumito took away my freedom.

194
00:23:06,470 --> 00:23:07,650
And...

195
00:23:10,610 --> 00:23:14,360
The videos that Itsuki had sent were just fragments,

196
00:23:14,360 --> 00:23:19,290
so I only saw bits and pieces of your life in Ukishima,

197
00:23:19,290 --> 00:23:24,220
but I could tell you were almost a different person now

198
00:23:24,220 --> 00:23:28,090
and that you were deceived by Fumito.

199
00:23:28,730 --> 00:23:33,840
You came to Tokyo to look for Fumito, didn't you?

200
00:23:33,840 --> 00:23:40,990
For the past six months, you've been coming around here and making trouble each time.

201
00:23:40,990 --> 00:23:43,080
However, none of this was reported in the news.

202
00:23:43,620 --> 00:23:45,160
If they were not reported…

203
00:23:45,160 --> 00:23:47,150
They could not hide them.

204
00:23:47,720 --> 00:23:52,540
In Japan, censorship of the internet is currently very strict,

205
00:23:52,540 --> 00:23:55,370
but we still have two good hackers.

206
00:24:00,880 --> 00:24:04,830
She is one of them — Tsukiyama Hiro-san.

207
00:24:08,520 --> 00:24:11,120
And the other is...

208
00:24:11,850 --> 00:24:16,380
The other is another story, but this is Fujimura Shu-kun.

209
00:24:16,380 --> 00:24:20,400
And the big one here is Matsuo Iori-kun.

210
00:24:20,400 --> 00:24:20,980
That's me.

211
00:24:21,460 --> 00:24:24,690
Mana introduced herself in the car, didn't she?

212
00:24:27,690 --> 00:24:32,010
I am Yanagi Haruno, a secretary of Mogari-san.

213
00:24:32,010 --> 00:24:36,160
These are all members of SIRRUT who come to this mansion.

214
00:24:37,080 --> 00:24:43,560
There are many others who support us on the internet.

215
00:24:43,560 --> 00:24:47,580
Everyone wants to abolish all the strange regulations and ordinances,

216
00:24:47,580 --> 00:24:52,980
such as the Juvenile Protection Curfew Ordinance and internet censorship.

217
00:24:54,530 --> 00:24:57,050
Where is Fumito now?

218
00:24:57,610 --> 00:25:01,230
These days, for his protection,

219
00:25:01,230 --> 00:25:06,060
his whereabouts are not being made public.

220
00:25:08,160 --> 00:25:09,730
Do you mean you don't know?

221
00:25:12,360 --> 00:25:14,400
I have ways of finding him.

222
00:25:14,400 --> 00:25:19,480
Members of SIRRUT connected through the network will...

223
00:25:19,480 --> 00:25:23,520
provide you with Fumito’s information.

224
00:25:23,520 --> 00:25:27,880
So, I need you to use your power to assist me, Kisaragi Saya.

225
00:25:39,970 --> 00:25:43,720
Nanahara Fumito is my prey.

226
00:25:49,690 --> 00:25:51,680
Do not forget that.

227
00:26:03,870 --> 00:26:07,080
Is it really okay to bring her into our group?

228
00:26:08,040 --> 00:26:09,020
Thank you.

229
00:26:11,230 --> 00:26:12,710
Here, Tsuki-chan.

230
00:26:12,710 --> 00:26:13,950
Thank you.

231
00:26:13,950 --> 00:26:15,510
What? Are you unsatisfied?

232
00:26:16,210 --> 00:26:19,130
No, it’s not that; I just don't like her attitude.

233
00:26:19,130 --> 00:26:22,510
There's no way we can trust her.

234
00:26:22,510 --> 00:26:25,470
She doesn't talk and she's so full of herself.

235
00:26:26,360 --> 00:26:29,160
But she is so beautiful.

236
00:26:29,980 --> 00:26:32,860
Ah, so you don’t care how she acts as long as she looks good?

237
00:26:32,860 --> 00:26:35,320
Did you forget about how she squeezed your cheeks?

238
00:26:35,320 --> 00:26:36,190
I give up.

239
00:26:36,600 --> 00:26:38,690
It’s Mogari-san’s decision.

240
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:46,620
I know that. But I still don’t like it.

241
00:26:46,620 --> 00:26:49,480
Tsuki-chan, you agree with me, don’t you?

242
00:26:50,740 --> 00:26:55,070
Tsuki-chan is upset because Mana can’t play with her.

243
00:26:55,070 --> 00:26:59,040
She has to show our new member around.

244
00:26:59,640 --> 00:27:03,510
Fuji-kun, I'm not gonna show you the cute cat video I downloaded yesterday...

245
00:27:03,510 --> 00:27:04,640
Nooooooo!

246
00:27:05,210 --> 00:27:06,650
You'll show it to me, won’t you?!

247
00:27:06,650 --> 00:27:07,640
Don’t bother Fuji.

248
00:27:07,640 --> 00:27:10,310
You are so mean, Matsu-san!

249
00:27:18,530 --> 00:27:20,540
Isn't this a huge mansion?

250
00:27:20,540 --> 00:27:24,600
Mogari-san is also the president of Sysnet, which is the most popular...

251
00:27:24,600 --> 00:27:26,980
company among recent graduates.

252
00:27:31,950 --> 00:27:35,760
Saya is... a beautiful name.

253
00:27:37,250 --> 00:27:40,810
Your last name, Kisaragi, is a very nice name as well.

254
00:27:41,390 --> 00:27:44,260
That is not my name.

255
00:27:45,810 --> 00:27:47,130
But...

256
00:27:50,090 --> 00:27:51,400
Oh, wait.

257
00:27:51,400 --> 00:27:53,600
This is your room.

258
00:27:56,750 --> 00:28:00,450
The bathroom is over there and a change of clothes is…

259
00:28:00,450 --> 00:28:01,480
This is fine.

260
00:28:01,480 --> 00:28:03,720
No, you have to wash them.

261
00:28:03,720 --> 00:28:06,870
I'll ask Yanagi-san for the clothes.

262
00:28:08,210 --> 00:28:09,320
Understood.

263
00:28:09,890 --> 00:28:15,420
Everyone else is commuting here from their homes,

264
00:28:15,420 --> 00:28:20,320
but I asked Mogari-san to let me live here.

265
00:28:20,320 --> 00:28:23,340
And my room is next to yours.

266
00:28:24,090 --> 00:28:27,740
So, if , if...

267
00:28:30,380 --> 00:28:38,700
if you're having any trouble or you need anything, let me know.

268
00:28:42,000 --> 00:28:45,370
I don’t need anything, but there is a place I want to go.

269
00:29:18,090 --> 00:29:19,570
Why are you following me?

270
00:29:20,530 --> 00:29:21,140
