00:50:18,990 --> 00:50:22,910
Tomorrow, Nanahara Fumito will be giving a lecture there.

538
00:50:22,910 --> 00:50:25,290
You're really something, managing to get your hands on this info.

539
00:50:25,890 --> 00:50:27,500
Regarding that... you see,

540
00:50:27,500 --> 00:50:30,700
we searched for loopholes in the network security...

541
00:50:30,700 --> 00:50:32,400
You mean Tsuki-chan did, right?

542
00:50:38,070 --> 00:50:39,380
Is this information reliable?

543
00:50:42,040 --> 00:50:44,260
Besides hacking skills,

544
00:50:44,260 --> 00:50:48,540
I was also taught the importance of determining the reliability of information, so...

545
00:50:50,800 --> 00:50:53,110
What will you do, Saya?

546
00:50:54,290 --> 00:50:55,130
I'll go.

547
00:50:55,560 --> 00:50:57,030
Hey wait,

548
00:50:57,030 --> 00:51:01,020
isn't it obvious that the school will have some unbelievably tight security?

549
00:51:01,020 --> 00:51:02,440
If you just go like that,

550
00:51:02,440 --> 00:51:05,860
you won't even be able to pass through the gate, much less get near Fumito.

551
00:51:05,860 --> 00:51:09,120
Regarding that, I've... I've worked hard on it!

552
00:51:09,120 --> 00:51:11,860
The locations of all the guards are at my fingertips!

553
00:51:11,860 --> 00:51:14,020
Fujimura-kun, you're really something!

554
00:51:15,410 --> 00:51:17,930
What about the uniform?

555
00:51:17,930 --> 00:51:20,600
Even if you infiltrate the school under the guise of a student,

556
00:51:20,600 --> 00:51:22,560
it's impossible to get your hands on one,

557
00:51:22,560 --> 00:51:25,310
and even if you wanted to make one, the lecture's tomorrow...

558
00:51:25,310 --> 00:51:26,130
Um...

559
00:51:26,130 --> 00:51:27,100
Huh?

560
00:51:27,260 --> 00:51:29,490
I may be able to help with the uniform.

561
00:51:29,490 --> 00:51:30,410
Huh?

562
00:51:39,760 --> 00:51:40,490
Wait.

563
00:52:00,250 --> 00:52:02,940
It doesn't look like it's going to stop raining.

564
00:52:04,530 --> 00:52:06,540
Wait up, Saya!

565
00:52:06,540 --> 00:52:08,270
The sound is great!

566
00:52:11,180 --> 00:52:13,500
The GPS is working perfectly too!

567
00:52:13,940 --> 00:52:18,500
But I didn't expect Mana-chan to be a student at Tsuji Private School...

568
00:52:22,050 --> 00:52:27,450
Hiiragi managed to tell Mogari-san herself that she'd be going.

569
00:52:28,700 --> 00:52:31,620
Please let me go with Saya.

570
00:52:32,090 --> 00:52:33,350
Please!

571
00:52:34,470 --> 00:52:35,500
Saya...

572
00:52:41,400 --> 00:52:42,660
Do as you see fit.

573
00:52:45,760 --> 00:52:48,730
We should give it everything we've got as well.

574
00:52:48,730 --> 00:52:49,780
Yeah!

575
00:52:49,780 --> 00:52:50,870
You're right.

576
00:52:52,280 --> 00:52:56,760
If they encounter any danger, make sure you rush in to the rescue, got it?

577
00:52:56,760 --> 00:52:57,670
Sure!

578
00:53:01,170 --> 00:53:03,170
I know you're worried,

579
00:53:03,750 --> 00:53:06,330
but let's provide as much support as we can, okay?

580
00:53:06,730 --> 00:53:07,660
Yes.

581
00:53:15,540 --> 00:53:19,480
You don't look like you're walking around in an unknown school.

582
00:53:20,300 --> 00:53:22,550
I'll stand out more if I'm on my guard.

583
00:53:22,550 --> 00:53:24,740
Y-You're right.

584
00:53:25,960 --> 00:53:27,270
Did you know?

585
00:53:27,270 --> 00:53:27,980
Huh?

586
00:53:28,850 --> 00:53:32,690
That this school has ties with them?

587
00:53:33,780 --> 00:53:34,650
Yes.

588
00:53:35,240 --> 00:53:38,110
A stone monument thanking them for their donations was erected,

589
00:53:38,110 --> 00:53:41,010
and the teachers told us about it.

590
00:53:43,560 --> 00:53:47,700
Actually, I wanted to leave this school, but...

591
00:53:50,240 --> 00:53:51,460
Hiiragi-san!

592
00:53:51,460 --> 00:53:52,160
Huh?

593
00:53:53,100 --> 00:53:54,280
You've come.

594
00:53:54,280 --> 00:53:55,790
Y-Yes.

595
00:53:56,190 --> 00:53:58,320
I thought you would be relaxing,

596
00:53:58,320 --> 00:54:00,100
since it's still winter break.

597
00:54:00,840 --> 00:54:03,270
It's troublesome for someone alone like you, isn't it?

598
00:54:03,270 --> 00:54:04,770
Are you all right?

599
00:54:04,770 --> 00:54:06,100
Y-Yes.

600
00:54:06,490 --> 00:54:09,480
There's the matter regarding your father too, so I guess it's inevitable,

601
00:54:09,480 --> 00:54:11,370
but I'm glad that you look well!

602
00:54:11,370 --> 00:54:14,290
Ah, it's almost time...

603
00:54:15,900 --> 00:54:16,770
Let's go.

604
00:54:26,200 --> 00:54:30,340
I'm glad that we don't have to sit according to our class.

605
00:54:30,340 --> 00:54:32,540
Our school is generally like that.

606
00:54:32,880 --> 00:54:34,290
What were you talking about just now...

607
00:54:34,290 --> 00:54:35,110
Huh?

608
00:54:35,110 --> 00:54:37,460
Regarding your father...

609
00:54:38,950 --> 00:54:40,710
Never mind, it's fine.

610
00:54:42,160 --> 00:54:43,920
Everyone, please be quiet.

611
00:54:45,120 --> 00:54:48,450
We'll start our special lecture now.

612
00:54:48,940 --> 00:54:51,660
The speaker will be Mr. Nanahara Fumito.

613
00:54:52,850 --> 00:54:55,460
Nanahara... isn't that Seventh Heaven's...

614
00:54:55,460 --> 00:54:56,510
Are you serious?

615
00:54:57,030 --> 00:54:59,880
So that's why we weren't allowed to bring in our mobile phones.

616
00:55:20,280 --> 00:55:21,270
What's going on?

617
00:55:23,540 --> 00:55:25,080
Please calm down.

618
00:55:25,700 --> 00:55:28,970
Please leave the lecture hall, following the instructions we have given.

619
00:55:31,280 --> 00:55:32,860
We should hurry up and leave.

620
00:55:32,860 --> 00:55:33,890
Saya!

621
00:55:43,860 --> 00:55:44,730
Mana!

622
00:55:45,120 --> 00:55:46,230
What's happening?

623
00:55:47,210 --> 00:55:48,960
I-I don't know!

624
00:55:48,960 --> 00:55:50,760
After the alarm went off, there were screams!

625
00:55:51,520 --> 00:55:54,120
But the school director's not moving at all!

626
00:55:59,200 --> 00:56:01,540
Saya, it's been a long time, hasn't it?

627
00:56:03,330 --> 00:56:04,000
Saya!

628
00:56:13,340 --> 00:56:15,300
Fumito!!!

629
00:56:23,070 --> 00:56:27,780
Saya, I'm sorry to disappoint you after you came all the way here.

630
00:56:28,550 --> 00:56:34,230
You're strong, so I thought it would be
troublesome if things remained this way.

631
00:56:34,770 --> 00:56:39,040
That's why... I'll play around with you a little.

632
00:56:53,480 --> 00:56:56,250
What... am I doing...

633
00:56:56,800 --> 00:56:57,760
Saya!

634
00:56:58,520 --> 00:56:59,560
Saya!

635
00:58:21,400 --> 00:58:23,340
S-Saya!

636
00:58:31,660 --> 00:58:32,670
Mana!

637
00:58:42,190 --> 00:58:43,270
Saya...

638
00:58:44,460 --> 00:58:45,450
Saya!

639
00:58:46,680 --> 00:58:47,790
Saya!

640
00:58:48,200 --> 00:58:49,380
Matsu-san!

641
00:58:49,380 --> 00:58:50,080
What?!

642
00:58:52,130 --> 00:58:53,670
Let's go!

643
00:58:54,370 --> 00:58:55,460
Fuji!

644
00:58:56,950 --> 00:58:58,670
Hold on tight!

645
00:59:01,560 --> 00:59:03,660
B-Blood...

646
00:59:37,020 --> 00:59:38,170
Saya.

647
01:00:14,600 --> 01:00:15,960
Mana, let's go!

648
01:00:16,320 --> 01:00:17,140
Sure.

649
01:00:32,260 --> 01:00:33,290
I'll go.

650
01:00:34,310 --> 01:00:36,320
The rest of you, hurry up with the collection.

651
01:00:46,940 --> 01:00:48,580
Saya, move aside please.

652
01:00:48,780 --> 01:00:50,190
I'll open it.

653
01:00:53,010 --> 01:00:54,500
So you're Saya.

654
01:00:57,720 --> 01:00:58,760
What's the matter?

655
01:00:59,640 --> 01:01:01,300
Does it hurt?

656
01:01:01,300 --> 01:01:03,470
You're a monster, just like that one you killed.

657
01:01:03,470 --> 01:01:04,400
Shut up!

658
01:01:19,350 --> 01:01:20,190
Saya!

659
01:01:20,700 --> 01:01:22,580
Don't worry about me!

660
01:01:24,140 --> 01:01:25,300
This is the end!

661
01:01:35,520 --> 01:01:37,420
You can't kill humans, right?

662
01:01:42,760 --> 01:01:43,820
Saya!

663
01:01:47,730 --> 01:01:51,820
That's why you're unable to protect anyone.

664
01:02:00,780 --> 01:02:01,690
Get in!

665
01:02:02,710 --> 01:02:03,900
Quickly!

666
01:02:15,930 --> 01:02:17,620
She needs treatment quickly!

667
01:02:23,280 --> 01:02:25,120
She escaped.

668
01:02:26,170 --> 01:02:27,370
Yeah.

669
01:02:28,720 --> 01:02:31,720
The blood collection went exactly as planned.

670
01:02:32,120 --> 01:02:34,390
We'll send it to the lab now.

671
01:02:35,120 --> 01:02:36,570
Thanks for the hard work.

672
01:02:49,090 --> 01:02:51,740
In other words, we were tricked.

673
01:02:53,520 --> 01:02:54,660
I'm sorry.

674
01:02:55,820 --> 01:02:56,920
Tsuki-chan...

675
01:02:57,720 --> 01:02:59,650
It's not your fault, Tsuki-chan.

676
01:03:01,200 --> 01:03:04,970
I allowed them to carry out the plan.

677
01:03:06,160 --> 01:03:07,520
It's my responsibility.

678
01:03:08,620 --> 01:03:09,780
Mogari-san.

679
01:03:10,440 --> 01:03:14,190
But I'm glad both of them managed to come back safely.

680
01:03:14,900 --> 01:03:18,580
Even though my car got wrecked again.

681
01:03:19,290 --> 01:03:21,180
It's an honorable battle scar.

682
01:03:21,560 --> 01:03:24,530
Well, someone did get injured.

683
01:03:24,530 --> 01:03:28,430
Compared to that, a little scratch is nothing...

684
01:03:29,060 --> 01:03:32,280
Didn't you have something against Saya-san?

685
01:03:33,080 --> 01:03:35,850
She got injured protecting Hiiragi, didn't she?

686
01:03:35,850 --> 01:03:39,210
Even though she could've ran away on her own if she had wanted to...

687
01:03:39,210 --> 01:03:43,060
I think I'm starting to see her in a new light.

688
01:03:44,460 --> 01:03:45,860
How's Saya-san?

689
01:03:46,230 --> 01:03:48,410
She said she's not going to the hospital,

690
01:03:48,410 --> 01:03:50,630
so Hiiragi got angry and ran after her.

691
01:03:52,130 --> 01:03:56,330
Wasn't Mana the one who hacked the lock on the lecture hall?

692
01:03:56,330 --> 01:03:57,740
I think so.

693
01:03:58,920 --> 01:04:01,560
Mana... cracked the code.

694
01:04:02,270 --> 01:04:03,540
Well, one thing led to another.

695
01:04:03,940 --> 01:04:06,480
And within such a short time...

696
01:04:06,480 --> 01:04:07,950
That's so like her.

697
01:04:08,400 --> 01:04:10,900
Now we have another outstanding hacker in our organization.

698
01:04:11,290 --> 01:04:12,500
I'm not outstanding at all!

699
01:04:12,960 --> 01:04:14,410
Mana's the amazing one!

700
01:04:14,920 --> 01:04:17,220
I'm just trying to keep up with what she taught me.

701
01:04:17,640 --> 01:04:19,300
She's totally out of my league.

702
01:04:21,500 --> 01:04:25,950
Will Mana go back to being a hacker because of this?

703
01:04:32,640 --> 01:04:33,680
No!

704
01:04:34,550 --> 01:04:36,020
You mustn't ignore your wounds!

705
01:04:37,430 --> 01:04:40,250
You can't possibly be fine after suffering such an injury!

706
01:04:40,250 --> 01:04:42,590
It's really not a big deal.

707
01:04:42,590 --> 01:04:43,150
Saya!

708
01:04:55,490 --> 01:04:57,410
I'm really sorry.

709
01:04:58,440 --> 01:05:00,640
You don't have to apologize.

710
01:05:02,930 --> 01:05:05,610
But it's...

711
01:05:05,610 --> 01:05:07,680
it's my fault.

712
01:05:08,800 --> 01:05:10,750
I've had enough.

713
01:05:15,450 --> 01:05:18,600
I'm really fine.

714
01:05:24,960 --> 01:05:27,440
The wounds have closed up.

715
01:05:28,000 --> 01:05:29,060
Why?

716
01:05:29,710 --> 01:05:33,040
Even if you don't know the reason, I'm telling you I'm fine.

717
01:05:33,820 --> 01:05:34,870
Do you understand now?

718
01:05:37,180 --> 01:05:38,480
Yeah.

719
01:05:38,480 --> 01:05:40,590
You said you've had enough?

720
01:05:41,720 --> 01:05:43,810
Did you have similar experiences before?

721
01:05:55,160 --> 01:06:00,140
My mother passed away early,
so it's just been me and my father.

722
01:06:00,780 --> 01:06:07,690
My father is bad at cooking, but he tried very hard to learn how to cook for me.

723
01:06:07,890 --> 01:06:14,480
Even though he was always busy with work, he gave it his all for my sake.

724
01:06:15,630 --> 01:06:18,620
You see, my father was a journalist.

725
01:06:20,750 --> 01:06:24,800
He loved reading the newspapers from back when articles were still printed on paper

726
01:06:25,410 --> 01:06:27,780
and delivered to the reader.

727
01:06:29,240 --> 01:06:32,110
When we met occasionally, he would always say that

728
01:06:32,760 --> 01:06:36,830
journalists needed to be curious and have inquisitive minds.

729
01:06:37,660 --> 01:06:39,770
He said that they have to be knowledgeable about a variety of things,

730
01:06:39,770 --> 01:06:41,950
remain unbiased by the information around them,

731
01:06:42,490 --> 01:06:45,220
and provide thorough coverage of the news.

732
01:06:45,920 --> 01:06:47,820
I was often reminded that

733
01:06:48,350 --> 01:06:52,580
once I made a decision, I should always stick with it to the end.

734
01:06:55,180 --> 01:07:01,160
A year ago, my father targeted Seventh Heaven for his next big scoop.

735
01:07:01,780 --> 01:07:04,970
However, he immediately received pressure from his superiors,

736
01:07:04,970 --> 01:07:06,850
and the coverage was discontinued.

737
01:07:06,850 --> 01:07:09,340
But that didn't stop my father.

738
01:07:09,680 --> 01:07:11,260
He said he would continue even on his own,

739
01:07:11,940 --> 01:07:14,500
and that he would definitely write an article on it.

740
01:07:17,070 --> 01:07:21,780
I thought I would be able to help my father, so I did some research.

741
01:07:24,050 --> 01:07:28,120
I only did it because I was so confident in my technological skills.

742
01:07:30,290 --> 01:07:33,250
I managed to hack into Seventh Heaven's system.

743
01:07:33,250 --> 01:07:35,450
That's when I found out how many people had gone there,

744
01:07:35,450 --> 01:07:39,700
and how most of them had disappeared.

745
01:07:41,140 --> 01:07:46,950
I also found out about the existence of something named "Tower".

746
01:07:47,830 --> 01:07:52,080
After gathering all the evidence, my father went off to meet with Nanahara Fumito.

747
01:07:53,360 --> 01:07:56,750
He... thanked me.

748
01:07:58,330 --> 01:08:03,420
And just like that, he was gone forever.

749
01:08:04,550 --> 01:08:07,850
If only I hadn't done such a thing!

750
01:08:07,850 --> 01:08:14,700
Father... my father didn't come back,

751
01:08:15,160 --> 01:08:17,440
and it's all my fault!

752
01:08:19,010 --> 01:08:20,780
I wanted to search for my father,

753
01:08:20,780 --> 01:08:22,760
so I joined this organization.

754
01:08:22,760 --> 01:08:24,570
But I was afraid to find out the truth,

755
01:08:24,570 --> 01:08:26,790
so I couldn't focus on hacking.

756
01:08:27,470 --> 01:08:31,010
What would I do if I found out that my father was dead?

757
01:08:41,930 --> 01:08:44,220
What about your father?

758
01:08:44,820 --> 01:08:45,820
I don't have one.

759
01:08:46,320 --> 01:08:49,980
However, I did have someone who was like a father to me.

760
01:08:53,520 --> 01:08:55,480
He was a kind person.

761
01:08:59,200 --> 01:09:02,140
Why are you so strong?

762
01:09:04,680 --> 01:09:06,890
I'm like your father.

763
01:09:06,890 --> 01:09:07,700
Huh?

764
01:09:08,220 --> 01:09:13,440
I make my own decisions,
and see them through to the very end.

765
01:09:13,810 --> 01:09:15,330
I had to find my resolve,

766
01:09:16,400 --> 01:09:19,200
so I could remain true to myself.

767
01:09:22,660 --> 01:09:23,770
I finally understand...

768
01:09:24,810 --> 01:09:28,140
why I couldn't leave you alone.

769
01:09:29,280 --> 01:09:32,160
We're pretty similar, aren't we?

770
01:09:33,400 --> 01:09:34,870
We're both lonely.

771
01:09:47,140 --> 01:09:49,940
Just as I thought, there's nothing written anywhere

772
01:09:49,940 --> 01:09:51,610
about that incident yesterday at Tsuji Private School.

773
01:09:52,160 --> 01:09:54,120
Geez... damn it!

774
01:09:55,320 --> 01:09:59,020
Mana-san and Saya-san didn't come, did they?

775
01:09:59,020 --> 01:10:01,010
She suffered so many injuries.

776
01:10:01,370 --> 01:10:03,690
Mana-chan's probably taking care of her.

777
01:10:04,360 --> 01:10:07,490
Actually, she really should go to the hospital.

778
01:10:08,730 --> 01:10:10,180
Good morning.

779
01:10:10,720 --> 01:10:11,840
Morning!

780
01:10:11,840 --> 01:10:13,740
Hey, you're lat—

781
01:10:14,260 --> 01:10:14,890
Sorry.

782
01:10:15,720 --> 01:10:17,960
I stayed up late last night.

783
01:10:19,990 --> 01:10:21,640
Tsuki-chan, good morning.

784
01:10:25,910 --> 01:10:27,070
Mana!

785
01:10:30,740 --> 01:10:34,780
Sorry for giving you bad information.

786
01:10:35,560 --> 01:10:38,240
You didn't lie to us on purpose, right?

787
01:10:38,240 --> 01:10:41,640
I would never do such... a thing!

788
01:10:41,640 --> 01:10:43,260
Then it's fine.

789
01:10:44,370 --> 01:10:46,650
As long as you weren't lying, it's okay.

790
01:10:51,130 --> 01:10:53,310
Does it hurt?

791
01:10:53,880 --> 01:10:54,720
No.

792
01:10:54,720 --> 01:10:55,920
Really?

793
01:10:55,920 --> 01:10:56,670
Yeah.

794
01:10:57,560 --> 01:11:00,250
I hope you recover from your injuries soon.

795
01:11:05,880 --> 01:11:08,610
Um, what am I saying?

796
01:11:09,050 --> 01:11:12,670
It seems that I was somewhat mistaken about you.

797
01:11:12,670 --> 01:11:15,700
Why do you sound so arrogant when you're supposed to be apologizing?

798
01:11:15,700 --> 01:11:16,960
Shut up!

799
01:11:19,000 --> 01:11:23,660
Anyway, thank you for protecting Hiiragi!

800
01:11:27,270 --> 01:11:29,440
Wha— are you ignoring me?!

801
01:11:29,440 --> 01:11:30,860
Now, now.

802
01:11:31,760 --> 01:11:35,930
Everyone, I've got something to tell you.

803
01:11:37,560 --> 01:11:39,140
Hacking?

804
01:11:39,380 --> 01:11:40,380
Yes.

805
01:11:41,210 --> 01:11:43,610
Mana-san, are you sure?

806
01:11:48,240 --> 01:11:49,410
I'm sure.

807
01:11:49,840 --> 01:11:52,840
I've realized that I need to stop running away and face my problems,

808
01:11:53,280 --> 01:11:56,620
no matter what the outcome will be.

809
01:11:57,490 --> 01:12:00,760
Hiiragi... I understand.

810
01:12:03,670 --> 01:12:06,970
After that incident at Tsuji Private School, it's very likely that Tower—

811
01:12:06,970 --> 01:12:11,030
or rather, Fumito will make a serious move to crush us.

812
01:12:11,730 --> 01:12:13,820
We should decide whether we need to fortify our defenses first,

813
01:12:14,280 --> 01:12:16,740
or head straight for the enemy headquarters.

814
01:12:17,470 --> 01:12:19,310
I would like everyone to consider these options.

815
01:12:19,310 --> 01:12:20,300
Yes, sir!

816
01:12:36,650 --> 01:12:40,290
It seems that you have a tendency to capture the hearts of those you encounter.

817
01:12:45,280 --> 01:12:48,190
I've done nothing.

818
01:12:53,570 --> 01:12:56,720
"Ask, and it shall be given;

819
01:12:57,330 --> 01:13:00,420
seek, and ye shall find;

820
01:13:00,420 --> 01:13:03,620
knock, and it shall be opened unto you."

821
01:13:04,300 --> 01:13:08,010
Man will find answers on his own.

822
01:13:10,140 --> 01:13:13,450
Saya, have you found your answer?

823
01:14:12,820 --> 01:14:13,500
Hm?

824
01:14:17,080 --> 01:14:17,860
Oh!

825
01:14:20,400 --> 01:14:22,330
Saya, you made this for me?

826
01:14:22,780 --> 01:14:24,950
I only poured what was already made.

827
01:14:25,500 --> 01:14:26,610
Thanks.

828
01:14:28,920 --> 01:14:30,590
Would you like to join me?

829
01:14:30,590 --> 01:14:31,660
I—

830
01:14:31,660 --> 01:14:34,350
Mogari-san made this for me.

831
01:14:34,350 --> 01:14:37,780
Everyone's been grateful to me
because I've been trying so hard.

832
01:14:38,420 --> 01:14:40,950
They said they wanted you to have some as well.

833
01:14:53,250 --> 01:14:54,800
Shouldn't you be sleeping?

834
01:14:54,800 --> 01:14:58,490
When I think I'm about to make a breakthrough, I just can't get to sleep.

835
01:14:58,490 --> 01:15:04,400
Besides, just like how you have your abilities, I have mine.

836
01:15:05,100 --> 01:15:06,050
I see.

837
01:15:20,160 --> 01:15:22,390
W-What's the matter?!

838
01:15:37,360 --> 01:15:38,660
I've found it!

839
01:15:40,940 --> 01:15:42,430
Tower's headquarters!

840
01:15:50,060 --> 01:15:53,110
Tokyo Bay Coastal Breakwater Landfill?

841
01:15:53,450 --> 01:15:54,440
Huh?

842
01:15:55,900 --> 01:15:58,400
She was really amazing.

843
01:15:58,400 --> 01:16:02,300
It didn't matter what security programs they were running—she was shredding them like paper.

844
01:16:03,560 --> 01:16:06,940
Why didn't you wake me up so I could witness the breakthrough?

845
01:16:08,240 --> 01:16:10,750
But there's nothing there.

846
01:16:11,260 --> 01:16:13,470
You can't find it in a residential search,

847
01:16:13,470 --> 01:16:17,210
but you can see it in an aerial view of the area.

848
01:16:22,460 --> 01:16:23,260
What?

849
01:16:24,830 --> 01:16:26,430
There's nothing.

850
01:16:26,430 --> 01:16:30,480
The satellite view had a fake photo embedded in it.

851
01:16:30,480 --> 01:16:31,950
Now let me remove it.

852
01:16:33,250 --> 01:16:34,140
Ah!

853
01:16:34,800 --> 01:16:35,980
Amazing.

854
01:16:36,740 --> 01:16:38,850
You really did a great job.

855
01:16:41,190 --> 01:16:44,830
Saya, we might find Fumito there.

856
01:17:00,120 --> 01:17:04,970
Damn, it's amazing how they were able to hide such a large facility.

857
01:17:04,970 --> 01:17:09,930
We're also amazing since we found it, right?

858
01:17:12,210 --> 01:17:13,400
Sure.

859
01:17:14,010 --> 01:17:17,000
Won't you let me go with you?

860
01:17:17,000 --> 01:17:18,020
No.

861
01:17:18,890 --> 01:17:21,020
They're armed.

862
01:17:21,020 --> 01:17:23,100
This is not your battle.

863
01:17:23,100 --> 01:17:24,960
But Saya, you'll be…

864
01:17:24,960 --> 01:17:28,520
You saw me. Minor injuries are nothing.

865
01:17:29,590 --> 01:17:33,790
Also, you've got more important things to worry about.

866
01:17:36,750 --> 01:17:40,300
You're right. I have to find my father.

867
01:17:46,170 --> 01:17:49,520
We'll do our best to support you.

868
01:17:49,520 --> 01:17:51,060
Are Tsuki-chan and Yanagi-san ready?

869
01:17:51,880 --> 01:17:53,790
We're ready and standing by.

870
01:17:59,110 --> 01:18:01,360
Tell us if something goes wrong.

871
01:18:01,360 --> 01:18:03,760
We'll try to stay put for as long as possible.

872
01:18:03,760 --> 01:18:06,390
If you think you can’t go on, just come back.

873
01:18:08,590 --> 01:18:09,520
Thank you.

874
01:18:15,080 --> 01:18:17,490
Okay. Let’s move.

875
01:19:04,030 --> 01:19:05,370
Where is the target?

876
01:19:17,500 --> 01:19:18,520
It started.

877
01:19:19,660 --> 01:19:23,150
Fuji-kun, please secure our communication line.

878
01:19:23,510 --> 01:19:24,410
Okay.

879
01:19:30,740 --> 01:19:33,950
Tsuki-chan, are you able to infiltrate their communications network?

880
01:19:34,380 --> 01:19:36,860
I've got their wireless communications.

881
01:19:36,860 --> 01:19:38,530
Can you tell how many people there are?

882
01:19:38,530 --> 01:19:39,290
Yes.

883
01:20:05,280 --> 01:20:08,570
Saya, I've got the number of people and their locations.

884
01:20:08,570 --> 01:20:11,110
The higher up you go, the more resistance you'll encounter.

885
01:20:11,110 --> 01:20:13,570
Nanahara Fumito must be on the top floor.

886
01:20:15,090 --> 01:20:16,090
No.

887
01:20:16,090 --> 01:20:16,810
Eh?

888
01:20:17,370 --> 01:20:23,290
Fumito's got something stronger than any human, and it doesn't need wireless communications.

889
01:20:23,290 --> 01:20:24,540
The Old Ones.

890
01:20:27,260 --> 01:20:28,710
What's the path of least resistance?

891
01:20:30,090 --> 01:20:31,130
The basement.

892
01:20:31,470 --> 01:20:32,480
Where is the entrance?

893
01:20:32,480 --> 01:20:33,320
Wait.

894
01:20:52,420 --> 01:20:53,820
Are you Fumito’s proxy?

895
01:20:56,600 --> 01:20:57,560
Saya?

896
01:20:59,080 --> 01:20:59,930
Continue.

897
01:21:00,550 --> 01:21:01,440
Right.

898
01:21:07,550 --> 01:21:10,460
You will not reach Fumito-sama.

899
01:21:21,340 --> 01:21:24,500
You look miserable, Kisaragi Saya.

900
01:21:27,800 --> 01:21:31,740
Don't say... that name.

901
01:21:40,190 --> 01:21:42,120
I've found the route to get to the basement.

902
01:21:42,760 --> 01:21:44,860
Go to the elevator hall all the way back,

903
01:21:44,860 --> 01:21:46,330
and take the right door.

904
01:21:46,940 --> 01:21:47,790
Saya?

905
01:21:49,950 --> 01:21:52,130
Kuto, it is not necessary any more.

906
01:21:57,860 --> 01:22:00,140
Yes, Fumito-sama.

907
01:22:02,840 --> 01:22:07,740
Look, this is what a person who would control the world can do.

908
01:22:53,220 --> 01:22:54,460
What is that sound?

909
01:22:54,460 --> 01:22:55,990
What the hell is going on?

910
01:22:55,990 --> 01:22:58,350
Saya, run straight.

911
01:22:58,350 --> 01:22:59,700
Hurry, Saya.

912
01:23:15,950 --> 01:23:18,590
Saya, next, turn left.

913
01:23:26,520 --> 01:23:29,670
You can go down all the way to the bottom from there.

914
01:23:47,310 --> 01:23:48,670
Saya.

915
01:23:48,670 --> 01:23:50,710
I'm fine. Don't worry.

916
01:24:38,340 --> 01:24:41,260
Good evening, Saya.

917
01:24:45,630 --> 01:24:47,060
This is…

918
01:24:50,560 --> 01:24:53,940
what the hell... is this?

919
01:24:55,980 --> 01:24:57,230
Stop.

920
01:24:58,530 --> 01:24:59,770
Stop!

921
01:25:01,600 --> 01:25:03,480
Saya, Saya! What’s wrong?

922
01:25:03,480 --> 01:25:04,570
Saya!

923
01:25:05,680 --> 01:25:06,740
Fumi...

924
01:25:07,480 --> 01:25:09,700
Saya! Saya!

925
01:25:10,840 --> 01:25:11,540
Fuji.

926
01:25:12,260 --> 01:25:14,500
I can’t do anything, the line's dead.

927
01:25:19,460 --> 01:25:22,810
I disabled the wireless communications because
I didn't want anyone to disturb us,

928
01:25:22,810 --> 01:25:26,010
now that we've finally gotten to meet face to face.

929
01:25:26,010 --> 01:25:27,300
I’m sorry.

930
01:25:28,630 --> 01:25:30,970
I'm really happy that you came to see me,

931
01:25:30,970 --> 01:25:35,270
but you shouldn't be causing so much damage.

932
01:25:48,130 --> 01:25:51,250
It's finally working, Kuroto.

933
01:25:52,350 --> 01:25:55,210
I gave her the amount that I was instructed.

934
01:25:55,940 --> 01:25:58,970
Has it just started working after moving around that much?

935
01:25:58,970 --> 01:26:00,250
What's with her?

936
01:26:10,430 --> 01:26:13,600
That cup of coffee...

937
01:26:17,160 --> 01:26:21,240
Why did I have to give her such a thing?

938
01:26:21,890 --> 01:26:27,640
All the kids at your place are nice kids with a strong sense of justice.

939
01:26:27,640 --> 01:26:31,550
They would never agree to drug her, would they?

940
01:26:33,580 --> 01:26:38,080
It doesn't work on humans, only you, Saya.

941
01:26:38,810 --> 01:26:41,550
Are you worried about the members of SIRRUT?

942
01:26:41,550 --> 01:26:43,390
You've become quite friendly with them,

943
01:26:44,280 --> 01:26:46,720
and that helped lure you here.

944
01:26:47,230 --> 01:26:50,430
You even drank the coffee, even though you were so cautious...

945
01:26:50,430 --> 01:26:53,310
and never ate anything offered to you before.

946
01:26:54,000 --> 01:26:56,730
They were quite useful.

947
01:26:57,580 --> 01:26:59,360
Don’t misunderstand.

948
01:26:59,360 --> 01:27:04,140
I did not deceive them, I used them.

949
01:27:05,200 --> 01:27:10,570
At first, SIRRUT was a very small internet group

950
01:27:10,570 --> 01:27:14,290
that wanted more freedom here in Japan, more specifically, in Tokyo.

951
01:27:15,630 --> 01:27:18,440
Well, I could've left them alone,

952
01:27:18,440 --> 01:27:22,480
but you never know how big things will get on the internet.

953
01:27:22,480 --> 01:27:27,620
That's why I offered to become their sponsor and provided funds.

954
01:27:29,090 --> 01:27:34,350
It made things easier since those brats believed any information I leaked.

955
01:27:34,350 --> 01:27:37,560
What's better, you came along,

956
01:27:37,560 --> 01:27:40,120
and they were able to lure you to the mansion.

957
01:27:41,490 --> 01:27:48,610
I didn't think Hiiragi would actually find this place.

958
01:27:49,370 --> 01:27:53,530
Well, I contacted Fumito right away.

959
01:27:54,520 --> 01:27:57,070
Now then, what are you going to do?

960
01:27:57,530 --> 01:28:01,980
Why are you spending so much time and money on one woman like this?

961
01:28:03,210 --> 01:28:05,920
Saya is special.

962
01:28:05,920 --> 01:28:11,210
Using so much of Seventh Heaven's money, and Tower's strength?

963
01:28:12,100 --> 01:28:12,890
Yes.

964
01:28:14,000 --> 01:28:19,260
You said you would dominate the world with your personal connections and power,

965
01:28:19,260 --> 01:28:23,730
along with controlling Tower by killing off both of our families.

966
01:28:24,130 --> 01:28:25,780
Yes, I did say that.

967
01:28:26,290 --> 01:28:30,530
We can expect even more money, power and fame ahead.

968
01:28:30,900 --> 01:28:32,610
I don’t need any of that.

969
01:28:33,860 --> 01:28:36,660
I said I wanted to have the world.

970
01:28:37,720 --> 01:28:39,620
That’s why bigger thinking…

971
01:28:39,620 --> 01:28:42,600
The world is small.

972
01:28:43,330 --> 01:28:47,130
It really is very small. Isn't it, Saya?

973
01:28:48,290 --> 01:28:50,740
This woman is the one?

974
01:28:59,080 --> 01:29:01,950
You've become careless, Fumito.

975
01:29:03,140 --> 01:29:05,810
Disappear here with this monster.

976
01:29:06,660 --> 01:29:09,370
I'll make it look like you were killed by this monster.

977
01:29:09,370 --> 01:29:11,740
Then I'll take everything.

978
01:29:13,660 --> 01:29:15,620
You underestimate me, cousin.

979
01:29:17,040 --> 01:29:19,170
You were always like that.

980
01:29:19,170 --> 01:29:21,660
Always looking down on me,

981
01:29:21,660 --> 01:29:22,960
that gaze enrages me!

982
01:29:33,350 --> 01:29:34,760
Fumito!

983
01:29:36,050 --> 01:29:39,860
I will keep the promise I made to you.

984
01:29:40,660 --> 01:29:42,780
Is this...

985
01:29:44,850 --> 01:29:46,640
Saya’s blood.

986
01:29:49,000 --> 01:29:53,550
Look, he's joined the covenant.

987
01:29:58,340 --> 01:30:05,180
Kuroto, you should now feel the power that you have been longing for.

988
01:30:10,100 --> 01:30:15,520
Saya, the key to controlling the man-eating Old Ones

989
01:30:15,520 --> 01:30:20,760
has been inherited and carried by the head of the Mogari family.

990
01:30:21,800 --> 01:30:27,590
Your blood is the only thing that can sever the ties between humans and the Old Ones.

991
01:30:30,320 --> 01:30:33,680
Curse you, I'll...

992
01:30:33,680 --> 01:30:35,680
Fumito...

993
01:30:40,890 --> 01:30:48,340
Saya, one cannot become human; one must be born human.

994
01:30:49,440 --> 01:30:52,030
You cannot kill humans.

995
01:30:52,030 --> 01:30:53,510
You are not human.

996
01:30:54,690 --> 01:30:59,370
The only thing that can satisfy your hunger is your own kind,

997
01:30:59,370 --> 01:31:01,370
the Old Ones.

998
01:31:02,130 --> 01:31:03,720
Did you know that...

999
01:31:03,720 --> 01:31:10,130
the human population is growing as rapidly as the Old Ones are disappearing?

1000
01:31:10,680 --> 01:31:13,390
Soon, there may be no need for the covenant.

1001
01:31:15,050 --> 01:31:18,720
Saya, how old are you now?

1002
01:31:19,320 --> 01:31:20,860
How many more years,

1003
01:31:21,630 --> 01:31:23,910
rather, how many more hundreds of years will you live?

1004
01:31:23,910 --> 01:31:27,120
During that time, the Old Ones may become extinct.

1005
01:31:27,740 --> 01:31:31,300
How will you survive if that happens?

1006
01:31:32,720 --> 01:31:33,880
Your blood.

1007
01:31:34,470 --> 01:31:39,470
I tried to use Tower's magic to create the Old Ones from humans,

1008
01:31:39,470 --> 01:31:41,980
but so far, I have not succeeded.

1009
01:31:41,980 --> 01:31:44,200
They die quickly.

1010
01:31:44,200 --> 01:31:51,200
I am doing my best... to gather people and missing persons.

1011
01:31:55,880 --> 01:31:57,700
Was it Mana-chan?

1012
01:31:58,920 --> 01:32:01,280
I saw the video from Mogari mansion.

1013
01:32:01,280 --> 01:32:03,300
Her father was a reporter, wasn't he?

1014
01:32:06,220 --> 01:32:09,080
He lived a little bit longer,

1015
01:32:10,200 --> 01:32:14,060
but he escaped and died the other day.

1016
01:32:14,950 --> 01:32:25,780
You sliced him to death right after you arrived in Tokyo, right, Saya?

1017
01:32:49,480 --> 01:32:51,040
What's going on?

1018
01:33:00,460 --> 01:33:04,500
You are truly beautiful, Saya.

1019
01:33:04,500 --> 01:33:06,590
The winner receives a reward.

1020
01:33:08,280 --> 01:33:13,240
This is the strongest power that I could create.

1021
01:33:20,650 --> 01:33:26,480
Previously, I could only run, but now look.

1022
01:34:29,040 --> 01:34:30,560
The Old Ones.

1023
01:35:08,750 --> 01:35:10,720
Those eyes.

1024
01:35:10,720 --> 01:35:13,900
They are the same as when I shot you.

1025
01:35:14,830 --> 01:35:17,150
They are so beautiful.

1026
01:35:17,150 --> 01:35:19,440
I want you, Saya.

1027
01:35:20,040 --> 01:35:22,060
Fumito!

1028
01:36:28,070 --> 01:36:29,470
Fumito.

1029
01:36:30,990 --> 01:36:34,240
Why are you doing this?

1030
01:36:43,200 --> 01:36:45,190
Here, Saya.

1031
01:36:45,490 --> 01:36:46,660
Fumito...

1032
01:36:47,880 --> 01:36:50,730
I told you, it's hard.

1033
01:36:51,630 --> 01:36:55,140
I tried it on myself right away.

1034
01:36:56,200 --> 01:36:58,910
If I could be the same thing that you are...

1035
01:37:04,270 --> 01:37:07,860
I could finally hold you.

1036
01:37:09,740 --> 01:37:11,550
I am sorry, Saya.

1037
01:37:11,550 --> 01:37:13,640
If I were a human,

1038
01:37:13,640 --> 01:37:18,300
your curse... would be broken.

1039
01:37:21,030 --> 01:37:26,060
As a winner, you receive a reward.

1040
01:37:26,690 --> 01:37:29,680
As a loser, I receive punishment.

1041
01:37:35,670 --> 01:37:39,440
You should have avoided me, Saya,

1042
01:37:40,360 --> 01:37:42,640
you turned it into a reward now...

1043
01:37:56,720 --> 01:37:58,760
I...

1044
01:38:00,250 --> 01:38:02,060
I ended up...

1045
01:38:04,350 --> 01:38:06,000
alone...

1046
01:38:20,650 --> 01:38:22,110
No way.

1047
01:38:22,110 --> 01:38:23,620
It's surrounded by police.

1048
01:38:24,780 --> 01:38:28,080
The area is off-limits, except to emergency vehicles.

1049
01:38:28,970 --> 01:38:33,420
We can’t get in touch with Mogari-san at all.

1050
01:38:34,150 --> 01:38:37,640
E-Excuse me, excuse me.

1051
01:38:55,790 --> 01:38:59,320
Yes, it is necessary to give young people freedom

1052
01:38:59,320 --> 01:39:01,240
in order to nurture them.

1053
01:39:01,720 --> 01:39:05,670
If you threaten them with harsh restrictions, only resistance will come out of it.

1054
01:39:05,670 --> 01:39:09,420
And it is imperative that adults do not deceive children...

1055
01:39:10,490 --> 01:39:13,920
Tsuki-chan, how were classes?

1056
01:39:13,920 --> 01:39:15,010
Mm-hm.

1057
01:39:15,010 --> 01:39:16,770
I stayed until the end.

1058
01:39:17,140 --> 01:39:19,080
Why don’t you join a club?

1059
01:39:19,080 --> 01:39:21,040
Clubs are boring.

1060
01:39:21,040 --> 01:39:23,740
It’s more fun playing with you guys.

1061
01:39:25,100 --> 01:39:26,040
Mana!

1062
01:39:27,510 --> 01:39:29,150
Hey!

1063
01:39:30,100 --> 01:39:36,760
Once she became the governor,
the internet restrictions were lifted.

1064
01:39:37,200 --> 01:39:40,370
The Juvenile Protection Curfew Ordinance was abolished as well.

1065
01:39:40,370 --> 01:39:43,360
It's like heaven compared to how it was back then.

1066
01:39:46,140 --> 01:39:49,820
Mogari-san... has disappeared, hasn’t he?

1067
01:39:51,960 --> 01:39:55,400
Sysnet was taken over by other companies,

1068
01:39:55,400 --> 01:39:58,980
and all of Seventh Heaven's executives have been replaced.

1069
01:39:58,980 --> 01:40:02,250
Nanahara Fumito has completely disappeared;

1070
01:40:02,250 --> 01:40:05,850
even the info about him on the internet is gone.

1071
01:40:06,670 --> 01:40:10,840
I am sorry for bringing up such a depressing topic.

1072
